@startuml User_Workflow
title User Workflow - Detect Parkinson or Not (Login to Result)

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontColor black
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowColor black
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor white
skinparam ActivityBorderColor black

start

:User opens the application;

:User logs in (register if new);

:Goal: Detect if person has Parkinson or not;

:User goes to upload or predict screen;

if (What does the user do?) then (Upload new data)
  :User chooses what to upload;
  note right
    SPEECH - audio file (voice recording)
    -> we extract 22 numbers: pitch, jitter, shimmer, voice stability

    HANDWRITING - image (spiral or sentence)
    -> we extract 10 numbers: pressure, tremor, fluency, stroke pattern

    GAIT - video (person walking)
    -> we extract 10 numbers: stride, speed, regularity, asymmetry

    Or COMBINED - one video for all three.
    These numbers are the input to detection.
  end note
  :User selects a file from device;
  :User clicks Upload;
  :System checks file (type, size);
  if (File OK?) then (yes)
    :System extracts features from the file;
    note right
      SPEECH: 22 numbers
      pitch, jitter, shimmer, voice stability

      HANDWRITING: 10 numbers
      pressure, tremor, fluency, stroke pattern

      GAIT: 10 numbers
      stride, speed, regularity, asymmetry

      These numbers are the input to detection.
    end note
    :User sees Features extracted successfully;
  else (no)
    :User sees error message (e.g. wrong file type or too large);
    stop
  endif
else (Already has features or uses examples)
  :User enters or uses extracted features;
endif

:User clicks Predict or Get result;

:System runs the model to detect Parkinson or not;
note right
  1. SE-ResNet 1D CNN - Learn patterns
  One encoder per modality. Learns: shaky voice, tremors,
  uneven strokes, irregular gait, slow speed.
  Patterns that can indicate Parkinson's.

  2. Attention Fusion - Weight modalities
  Learns which modality to trust more for this person.
  More weight on speech, or handwriting, or gait.
  Then combines into one representation for detection.

  3. Dense classifier - Binary decision
  PARKINSON: when patterns show tremor, slowness, irregularity
  (shaky voice, tremulous writing, uneven walk).
  NOT PARKINSON (Healthy): when patterns are normal
  (steady voice, smooth writing, regular walk).
  Output: one of two classes with confidence.
end note

:System produces detection result;

:User sees the detection result on screen;
note right
  Parkinson's detected - e.g. 92 percent confidence
  or Not Parkinson (Healthy) - e.g. 88 percent confidence.

  In short: numbers in -> detect Parkinson or not -> result out.
end note

:User can log out or do another detection;

stop

@enduml
